claims:
Claims 1. A process for producing carburised molten metal (15) in a smelting apparatus (1), with the apparatus including a smelting vessel (2) that is adapted to contain a bath of molten metal (6) and a slag layer (7), and with the process including the steps of: vi. providing the bath of molten metal (6) and the slag layer (7) in the smelting vessel (2), characterised in that vii. injecting pure oxygen gas (8) into the smelting vessel (2) above the slag layer (7), injecting a first stream of solid metalliferous feed material (11) into the molten metal (6) or slag layer (7) in the smelting vessel (2), and injecting solid carbon containing compounds (10) and/or carbon containing gas (9) into or above the molten metal (6) or slag layer (7) in the smelting vessel (2) for heating and melting the solid metalliferous feed material (11), for reducing any metallic oxide compounds present in the solid metalliferous feed material (11), and for carburising the molten metal (6) in the smelting vessel (2) to a desired carbon content to produce carburised molten metal (15); viii. discharging the hot and (optionally partially) combustible and reducing process gas (14) comprising CO? , CO, H 2 O and H 2 compounds in the smelting vessel upwardly out of the smelting vessel (2); ix. discharging carburised molten metal (6) with the desired carbon content from the smelting vessel (2), preferably in a continuous manner; x. discharging molten slag (7) from the smelting vessel (2), preferably separate from the carburised molten metal, preferably in a continuous manner. 2. Process according to claim 1, wherein the first stream of solid metalliferous feed material (11) consists mainly of solid ferriferous feed material, and wherein the carburised molten metal (15) comprises or consists mainly of molten iron. 3. Process according to claim 2, wherein the solid ferriferous feed material (11) comprises one or more of direct reduced iron, hot briquetted iron, cold briquetted iron, solidified pig iron, ferrous scrap, optionally in combination with iron oxides or iron ore. 4. Process according to claim 2 or 3, wherein the solid feed ferriferous material (11) consists substantially of one or more of direct fully reduced iron, hot briquetted iron, cold briquetted iron, solidified pig iron, ferrous scrap. 5. Process according to any one of claims 1 to 4, wherein the smelting apparatus (1) also includes a smelt cyclone (3) that is positioned above the smelting vessel (2) in open connection with the smelting vessel (2) so as to form a single reactor therewith. 6. Process according to claim 5, wherein the process including the further steps of: vii. leading the hot and (optionally partially) combustible and reducing process gas (14) resulting from one or more of f. the heating and melting the solid metalliferous feed material (11), and g. the reduction of any metallic oxide compounds present in the solid metalliferous feed material (11), and h. the carburisation of the molten metal (6) in the smelting vessel (2) to a desired carbon content, and i. the release of volatiles from injected carbon containing gas, and j. residual reducing components from excess injected carbon containing gas; upwardly out of the smelting vessel (2) through the smelt cyclone (3); viii. introducing a second stream of metalliferous feed material (11') into the smelt cyclone (3) and partially reducing said second stream of metalliferous feed material (11') in the smelt cyclone by means of the hot and (at least partially) combustible and reducing process gas (14) originating from the smelting vessel (2); ix. effecting a post-combustion of the hot and (at least partially) combustible and reducing process gas (14) in the melting cyclone (3) by supplying oxygen thereto so that said second stream of metalliferous feed material (11') is at least partly melted and at least partly reduced in the melting cyclone (3); x. upwardly discharging an off-gas (17) from the smelt cyclone (3); xi. permitting the said at least partly melted and at least partly reduced second stream of metalliferous feed material (11') to pass downwardly from the melting cyclone (3) into the smelting vessel (2); 

 xii. effecting the final reduction and melting of the partially reduced first and second streams of metalliferous feed material (11, 11') and effecting the carburation of the molten metal to the desired carbon content to produce carburised molten metal (15) by the injected oxygen gas (8) and the injected solid carbon containing compounds (10) and/or the carbon containing gas (9). 7. Process according to any one of claims 1 to 6, wherein the desired carbon content of the carburised molten metal (15) is at least 3.0 wt.%. 8. Process according to any one of claims 1 to 7, wherein the carburised molten metal (15) is further processed in an electric arc furnace. 9. Process according to any one of claims 1 to 8, wherein the carburised molten metal (15) is further processed in a reducing electric arc furnace. 10. Process according to any one of claims 1 to 9, wherein the carburised molten metal (15) is further processed in a conventional steelmaking plant, such as an LD-plant or KOBM. 11. Process according to any one of claims 6 to 10, wherein the second stream of solid metalliferous feed material (11') also comprises returns from the iron and steel production such as metalliferous dusts, mill scale, steelmaking slag, and sludge. 12. Process according to any one of claims 6 to 11, wherein the carbon containing compounds (10, 10') comprises coal, charcoal, cokes, graphite or biomass, or returns from the iron and steel production such as carbonaceous dusts. 13. Process according to any one of claims 6 to 12, wherein the second stream of solid metalliferous feed material (11') comprises iron ore. 14. Process according to claim 10 wherein the carburised molten metal (15) is processed into steel. 15. Use of the process according to any one of the claims 1 to 13 to produce a carburised molten metal (15) having a carbon content of at least 3.0 wt.%, preferably wherein the carburised molten metal is carburised molten iron (15). 16. Apparatus (1) for the production of carburised molten iron (15) according to any one of claims 4 to 13, comprising a. a smelting vessel (2); b. supply means for supplying coal (10), in operation of the apparatus, into or above the molten metal (6) or into the slag layer (7) in the smelting vessel 

 (2) above a molten bath of iron (6) in the smelting vessel (2) or into the molten metal (6); c. supply means (8) for supplying pure oxygen into the smelting vessel (2), d. discharge means for discharging carburised molten iron (15) and molten slag (16) from the smelting vessel (2), e. a smelt cyclone (3) located above and in open connection with the smelting vessel (2) so as to form a single reactor therewith, enabling combustible and reducing process gas to pass, in operation, from the smelting vessel (2) directly into the melting cyclone (3) and at least partially melted pre-reduced iron ore passing from the melting cyclone directly into the smelting vessel (2); f. supply means for supplying iron ore into the smelt cyclone (3), g. supply means for supplying oxygen into the smelt cyclone (3), h. discharge means (18) for discharging process off-gas (17) from the smelt cyclone (3), i. optionally a steam-producing boiler (19) in the discharge means for generating steam from sensible heat contained in the process off-gas (17), j. optionally dedusting means (20) downstream of the optional steamproducing boiler (19) for dedusting the process off-gas (17).
